Description

The Bacula Agent Deploy Server (BADS) is a simple web server writed on Golang for managing and deploying Backup Bacula Agent (bacula-client and configuration files) on host.
This web solution uses Ansible playbook for automation installation Bacula Agent in users` hosts.
NOTE: BADS is a Open-source projects. I am grateful @opast (https://github.com/opast) for initial help!

Installation

# Deploy Bacula Agent Deploy Server
cd /opt
Clone repo to folder git clone https://github.com/MykolaPerehinets/bads.git
cd /opt/bads
Verify configuration in /opt/bads/templates/todo.html
Run ./install.sh

# Update Bacula Agent Deploy Server
cd /opt/bads
Pull repo to folder git pull https://github.com/MykolaPerehinets/bads.git
Verify configuration in /opt/bads/templates/todo.html
Run ./install.sh

# Rsync Bacula Agent Deploy Server
rsync -uvroghtpaz --rsync-path="ionice -c 3 nice -n 12 rsync" --progress --stats "/home/mperehin/LOG_FOR WORK/bads" root@ibacula.localhost.localdomain:/opt/

Information and usage
https://localhost.localdomain:8443
default username: admin
default password: admin

This folder contains a collection of Go programs and libraries
cd /opt/bads
cat ./bads.go
